Because if its the second one, then you have to do that inside of your hubl Code.

Add some form of _if_-Statement around the divs that you dont want to display.


```{% if item.amount &lt; 6 %}
&lt;div class="RequestButton"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="ContactUs"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
{% endif %}```

okay, i think you should consider to add a toggle field in your options. then the person that has to add it can manage if it should show the button or not.
the idea would be very similar to what i suggested before: wrap the button you want to hide inside of an if check.

so something like:
```{% if item.new_toggle_field %}
&lt;div class="Price"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt; 
{% endif %}```
